        <mxCell id="U-vC1FSZheFBAanJOaOG-5" parent="1" style="shape=image;imageAspect=0;aspect=fixed;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;verticalAlign=top;image=data:image/png,;shadow=0;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="280" width="539.26" x="55" y="630" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="U-vC1FSZheFBAanJOaOG-7" parent="1" style="shape=image;imageAspect=0;aspect=fixed;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;verticalAlign=top;image=data:image/png,;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="234" width="845" x="20" y="980" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="U-vC1FSZheFBAanJOaOG-8" parent="1" style="shape=image;imageAspect=0;aspect=fixed;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;verticalAlign=top;image=data:image/png,;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="558.57" width="488.75" x="20" y="1260" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="U-vC1FSZheFBAanJOaOG-10" parent="1" style="shape=image;imageAspect=0;aspect=fixed;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;verticalAlign=top;image=data:image/png,;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="377.88" width="750" x="50" y="2180" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="U-vC1FSZheFBAanJOaOG-11" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h4 data-path-to-node=&quot;9&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;9&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Handling Likes &amp;amp; Comments (Non-Pub-Sub Model)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot;&gt;Since we are avoiding the Pub-Sub model (like Kafka/RabbitMQ), we implement a &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;78&quot;&gt;Synchronous Write with Read-Optimized View&lt;/b&gt; strategy to handle massive scale.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Likes (Atomic Increments):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,1,0,1,0&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,1,0,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-83&quot;&gt;Write Path:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-83&quot;&gt; When a user clicks &quot;Like,&quot; the request is routed through the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,1,0,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;73&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-83&quot;&gt;API Gateway&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-83&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,1,0,1,1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-83 citation-end-83&quot;&gt;&lt;sup class=&quot;superscript&quot; data-turn-source-index=&quot;11&quot;&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,1,0,1,2&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; to an &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,1,0,1,2&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;7&quot;&gt;Interaction Service&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,1,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Atomic Storage:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; Instead of updating a standard relational row, the system uses &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;11,0,1,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;79&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Atomic Increments&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; in a fast NoSQL store (like Redis or DynamoDB). This allows millions of users to update the same video&#39;s like-count simultaneously without database locks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Comments (Database Sharding):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,1,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Partitioning:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; Comments are stored in a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,1,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;39&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Sharded Database&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; (e.g., PostgreSQL Sharded), where the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,1,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;94&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Video_ID&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; is used as the sharding key. This ensures that all comments for a specific video are stored on the same node for fast retrieval.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,1,1,0,0&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,1,1,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Read Path:&lt;/b&gt; To prevent overloading the database during high-traffic &quot;viral&quot; events, the system utilizes &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,1,1,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;103&quot;&gt;Metadata Caching&lt;/b&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,1,1,0,1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-82&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,1,1,0,2&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;The top comments and like counts are cached at the CDN or API Gateway level and returned in the initial Video Metadata response&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,1,1,0,3&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-82 citation-end-82&quot;&gt;&lt;sup class=&quot;superscript&quot; data-turn-source-index=&quot;12&quot;&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-path-to-node=&quot;11,1,1,1,0,4&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="310" width="890" x="-2.5" y="1840" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
